# 12. Troubleshooting Guide

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Issue**               **Solution**
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  Claude API returns 401  Check API key in the Code node. Verify the
                          corpfit-quantum key is active in Anthropic
                          console.

  \'fetch is not          Use this.helpers.httpRequest() instead.
  defined\' in Code node  Standard fetch() and \$http are NOT available
                          in n8n Code nodes.

  Qdrant returns empty    Verify collection names are corpfit_brand_rules
  results                 and corpfit_banned_phrases (not funfit\_\*).
                          Check dashboard at localhost:6333.

  QA gates return         Haiku sometimes wraps JSON in markdown fences.
  PARSE_ERROR             The robust parser handles this, but if issues
                          persist, check raw response in gate output.

  All content gets        Check Gate 1 prompt --- it may be too strict.
  BLOCKED                 Ensure the \'LENIENT on wellness\' tuning is in
                          place. Review gate1_violations for false
                          positives.

  Sub-workflow receives   Known n8n limitation. Use inline Code nodes
  empty data              instead of Execute Sub-Workflow. This is why v6
                          uses inline gates.

  PostgreSQL insert fails Verify connection uses postgres:5432 (Docker
                          name). Check table exists: docker exec -it
                          postgres psql -U user -d corpfit -c \'\\dt\'

  Docker service          Use container names (qdrant, ollama, postgres)
  unreachable             NOT localhost in n8n Code nodes. Run \'docker
                          ps\' to verify containers.

  Output parsing returns  Check Claude\'s raw response for emoji headers.
  empty fields            If missing, the UAF-1.0 prompt may have been
                          truncated.

  Template literals cause Use string concatenation (\'a\' + \'b\')
  SyntaxError             instead of template literals (\`\${a}\`) in n8n
                          Code nodes when copy-pasting.
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# 13. Key Technical Lessons

Critical discoveries made during Days 1-10 that you should never forget:

19. **Lesson 1:** n8n Code nodes use this.helpers.httpRequest() for HTTP
    calls. fetch() and \$http do NOT work.

20. **Lesson 2:** Use Docker container names (qdrant, ollama, postgres),
    never localhost, for inter-service communication.

21. **Lesson 3:** String concatenation (\'a\' + b) works reliably in n8n
    Code nodes. Template literals (\`\${b}\`) can cause SyntaxError when
    copy-pasting.

22. **Lesson 4:** n8n sub-workflows do NOT reliably pass JSON data
    through Execute Sub-Workflow triggers. Use inline Code nodes
    instead.

23. **Lesson 5:** Claude Haiku sometimes wraps JSON responses in
    markdown code fences (\`\`\`json\`\`\`). Always include a robust
    parser with regex fallback.

24. **Lesson 6:** QA gate prompts must match the platform context. A
    wellness app encouraging walking is different from a medical site.
    \'STRICT on everything\' causes false positives.

25. **Lesson 7:** Local AI models (llama3.2:3B, llama3.1:8B) are too
    weak for complex 3,300-word prompts. Claude Sonnet 4 via API is the
    right choice.

26. **Lesson 8:** The hybrid RAG approach (static core + dynamic Qdrant
    knowledge) is highly effective. You can update brand rules without
    changing the workflow.

27. **Lesson 9:** Sequential QA gates save money --- if Gate 1 fails,
    Gates 2 and 3 still run but could be skipped in future optimization.

28. **Lesson 10:** Always pass ALL fields through every node using the
    \'copy all keys\' pattern. Losing fields between nodes is the #1
    cause of bugs.

-   **Lesson 11:** n8n HTTP Request nodes cannot handle complex JSON
    body interpolation with quotes/special characters. Use Code nodes
    with this.helpers.httpRequest() instead for API calls that need
    dynamic content.

-   **Lesson 12:** Claude Haiku model string is
    claude-3-5-haiku-20241022 (NOT claude-haiku-4-5). Using the wrong
    model name returns a 404 error from the Anthropic API.

-   **Lesson 13:** Reddit JSON endpoints (e.g.
    reddit.com/r/fitness/hot.json) return nested data structures ---
    each response contains multiple posts that need to be unpacked
    individually during normalization (33 raw items became 51
    normalized).

